    "body": "It can only work if `expose()` is marked `external`, while if `internal`/`public` it would be a declaration clash. Technically it is fine.\r\n\r\nConsidering the reliance on visibility, it may not be a good idea to allow it to avoid confusion (and potential future issues).\r\n",
